olive oil
1 packet peeled pumpkin pieces
1 potato
1 beetroot
1 packet Mild Chorizo
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 packet Baby Leaves
drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut potato and beetroot into bite-sized chunks. Finely chop mild chorizo.
• Place peeled pumpkin pieces, potato and beetroot on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, toss to coat and spread out evenly. Bake until browned and tender, 20-25 minutes.

TIP: If your oven tray is crowded, divide the veggies between two trays.

• When veggies have 15 minutes remaining, remove tray from the oven.
• Add chorizo to the tray. Sprinkle over grated Parmesan cheese.
• Roast until veggies are tender and cheese is melted, 10-15 minutes.

• Meanwhile, roughly chop baby leaves.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook baby leaves until tender, 2-3 minutes.
• When the cheesy veggies and chorizo are done, add baby leaves and a drizzle of white wine vinegar to the tray. Season to taste.
• Gently toss to combine.

• Divide cheesy chorizo and veggie traybake between plates.
• Serve with a dollop of dill & parsley mayonnaise. Enjoy!